      "acceptanceCriteria": "Achieved level must meet or exceed required level of 3 for Model Risk Level 3.",
      "rationale": "All three FEA codes (FDA in-house, Ansys 2021 R2, DePuy Synthes internal) operate under documented software quality management systems with version control, regression test suites, and release validation records. ISO 9001-compliant QMS documented for each code instance. Achieved level equals required level."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Numerical code verification",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Achieved level must meet or exceed required level of 3.",
      "rationale": "Benchmark problems including patch tests, single-element tests, and published NAFEMS benchmarks were executed for each solver. Results match analytic solutions within 0.5% for linear elastic cases. Code verification documentation archived per ASME V&V 10.1."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Discretization error",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Achieved level must meet or exceed required level of 3; mesh convergence study required.",
      "rationale": "Systematic h-refinement convergence study performed across three mesh densities (coarse, medium, fine). Richardson extrapolation applied; discretization error in peak von Mises stress at screw-rod interface estimated at less than 2.1%. Grid Convergence Index reported."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Numerical solver error",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Achieved level must meet or exceed required level of 2.",
      "rationale": "Iterative solver residuals monitored; force and displacement residual norms converged below 1e-6 for all load steps. Direct solver cross-check performed on representative sub-models confirming agreement within 0.1%. No spurious energy modes detected."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Use error",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Achieved level must meet or exceed required level of 3; independent review of model setup required.",
      "rationale": "Independent analyst review of boundary conditions, material assignments, contact definitions, and load application performed by a reviewer not involved in model construction. Discrepancies identified and corrected prior to final simulation runs. Formal model review checklist completed and archived."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model form",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Achieved level must meet or exceed required level of 3; constitutive model selection justified.",
      "rationale": "Linear elastic isotropic constitutive models applied to titanium alloy components consistent with sub-yield loading regime of ASTM F1717. Contact modeled with penalty-based frictional formulation (mu=0.2 per literature). Geometric nonlinearity included for large-displacement compression-bending path. Justification documented against published material characterization data."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model inputs",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Achieved level must meet or exceed required level of 3; material properties and geometry traceable to measurements.",
      "rationale": "Ti-6Al-4V elastic modulus (114 GPa) and yield strength (880 MPa) sourced from certificate of conformance and independent coupon testing. Screw and rod geometry digitized from CMM measurements of production components. UHMWPE block geometry per ASTM F1717 fixture specification. Full input traceability matrix archived."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test samples",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Achieved level must meet or exceed required level of 3; N >= 10 specimens from production lots.",
      "rationale": "N=11 non-cannulated 7.5 mm pedicle screw constructs tested; specimens drawn from three production lots to capture manufacturing variability. Dimensional inspection performed on all specimens prior to testing. Sample size justification documented per statistical power analysis."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test conditions",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Achieved level must meet or exceed required level of 3; multiple test conditions spanning clinical loading range required.",
      "rationale": "Testing performed at a single load angle (10 degrees) per ASTM F1717 standard protocol. Clinical loading range spans multiple angulations; only one condition tested. This factor falls below required level and represents a known gap accepted by the credibility assessment team given the scope of the regulatory submission. Risk accepted at program level."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Equivalency of input parameters",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Achieved level must meet or exceed required level of 3; simulation inputs matched to experimental conditions.",
      "rationale": "FEA boundary conditions replicate ASTM F1717 fixture geometry, grip separation (100 mm), and load application point. Measured specimen dimensions used as FEA geometry inputs. Friction coefficient validated against instrumented fixture measurements. Parameter equivalency table cross-referencing experimental and simulation inputs archived."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Output comparison",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Achieved level must meet or exceed required level of 3; quantitative comparison metrics with uncertainty bounds required.",
      "rationale": "Quantities of interest (construct stiffness and 2% offset yield load) compared between FEA ensemble and experimental mean using validation metric V = (sim - exp_mean) / exp_std. All three FEA codes yield V within [-1.5, +1.5] for stiffness and yield load. Experimental uncertainty quantified via Type A evaluation. Graphical and tabular comparisons archived."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the quantities of interest",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Achieved level must meet or exceed required level of 3; QOIs must be directly linked to regulatory decision.",
      "rationale": "Construct stiffness and yield load are the primary mechanical performance endpoints specified in FDA guidance for posterior spinal fixation systems. These QOIs directly inform the 510(k) substantial equivalence determination. Clinical relevance documented through linkage to predicate device performance data."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the validation activities to the COU",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Achieved level must meet or exceed required level of 3; validation scenario must be representative of the intended use context.",
      "rationale": "Validation activity uses production-representative non-cannulated 7.5 mm pedicle screw constructs tested per ASTM F1717, which is the regulatory standard for posterior spinal fixation. Test configuration, specimen geometry, and loading mode directly correspond to the intended pre-market design verification use. Relevance mapping table archived linking each validation element to the intended use scope described in the claim and requirement documentation."
    }
  ],
